1
00:00:01,503 --> 00:00:05,010
Lecturer: Where we have the index get action method,

2
00:00:05,010 --> 00:00:08,163
we are populating the shopping cart view model.

3
00:00:09,120 --> 00:00:10,770
But in that view model,

4
00:00:10,770 --> 00:00:12,900
if we press F12 here,

5
00:00:12,900 --> 00:00:17,220
we have the OrderTotal that we have to calculate.

6
00:00:17,220 --> 00:00:21,423
Calculating that OrderTotal is a little bit tricky,

7
00:00:22,770 --> 00:00:26,463
because based on the quantity we have different price.

8
00:00:27,330 --> 00:00:30,120
Like if we have this book for an example,

9
00:00:30,120 --> 00:00:32,670
if the quantity is between one to 50,

10
00:00:32,670 --> 00:00:34,740
the price is $30.00,

11
00:00:34,740 --> 00:00:37,140
more than 50 it's $25.00,

12
00:00:37,140 --> 00:00:40,470
and more than 100 it is $20.00.

13
00:00:40,470 --> 00:00:44,370
When we display the OrderTotal we need a helper method,

14
00:00:44,370 --> 00:00:46,890
that will calculate based on quantity,

15
00:00:46,890 --> 00:00:49,233
which price should be utilized.

16
00:00:50,340 --> 00:00:52,560
So let me create that helper

17
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:56,073
inside the Cart Controller right here.

18
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:59,490
We can make that method a private method.

19
00:00:59,490 --> 00:01:01,470
Return type will be double,

20
00:01:01,470 --> 00:01:03,933
and let me call that GetPriceBasedOnQuantity.

21
00:01:05,828 --> 00:01:10,230
And the parameter here we will be passing ShoppingCart,

22
00:01:10,230 --> 00:01:12,540
and that looks good.

23
00:01:12,540 --> 00:01:14,160
Based on that we can check

24
00:01:14,160 --> 00:01:15,137
if(ShoppingCart.Count <= 50).

25
00:01:20,419 --> 00:01:21,252
In that case,

26
00:01:21,252 --> 00:01:23,910
we want to return the default price,

27
00:01:23,910 --> 00:01:28,910
so that we have inside ShoppingCart.Product.Price;

28
00:01:30,660 --> 00:01:34,110
In the else part here we will have an if condition.

29
00:01:34,110 --> 00:01:35,177
If (ShoppingCart.Count <= 100),

30
00:01:39,607 --> 00:01:42,480
In that case we want to return

31
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:46,890
ShoppingCart.Product.Price50;

32
00:01:46,890 --> 00:01:49,380
It has to be less than 100,

33
00:01:49,380 --> 00:01:52,590
else if it is greater than 100 then we will

34
00:01:52,590 --> 00:01:56,883
return ShoppingCart.Product.Price100;

35
00:01:58,200 --> 00:01:59,370
Based on that,

36
00:01:59,370 --> 00:02:01,620
whatever cart we pass here,

37
00:02:01,620 --> 00:02:04,803
we will know what is the price that we have to use.

38
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:08,460
Right here where we have the ShoppingCart view model,

39
00:02:08,460 --> 00:02:11,550
we have to iterate through each one of the cart.

40
00:02:11,550 --> 00:02:12,497
So (variable cart in ShoppingCartVM.ShoppingCartList).

41
00:02:16,647 --> 00:02:19,080
We have the ShoppingCartList there,

42
00:02:19,080 --> 00:02:23,070
and we have to calculate the Cart.Price.

43
00:02:23,070 --> 00:02:24,480
Right here we can add a

44
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:29,480
double price = GetPriceBasedOnQuantity,

45
00:02:29,640 --> 00:02:32,400
and we will pass the shopping cart.

46
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:33,990
Now using that price,

47
00:02:33,990 --> 00:02:35,191
we can calculate the

48
00:02:35,191 --> 00:02:39,168
ShoppingCartVM.OrderTotal

49
00:02:39,168 --> 00:02:43,418
+= (price * cart.Count).

50
00:02:45,810 --> 00:02:46,643
Perfect.

51
00:02:46,643 --> 00:02:48,150
I believe that looks good.

52
00:02:48,150 --> 00:02:50,670
Let me restart the application,

53
00:02:50,670 --> 00:02:54,363
and see if we are able to calculate the total price.

54
00:02:56,010 --> 00:02:58,530
Let me go to our shopping cart,

55
00:02:58,530 --> 00:03:01,440
and we examine the view model.

56
00:03:01,440 --> 00:03:02,430
Perfect.

57
00:03:02,430 --> 00:03:05,100
We have an order total here based on

58
00:03:05,100 --> 00:03:08,343
the price and the count that has been added.

59
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:11,250
So some number is coming up,

60
00:03:11,250 --> 00:03:12,810
if that is true or false,

61
00:03:12,810 --> 00:03:15,300
we will see in the upcoming lectures.

62
00:03:15,300 --> 00:03:18,600
But right now this logic is working.

63
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:20,880
Now one thing that I want to modify is,

64
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:23,673
what if I want to display this price on the UI?

65
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:27,363
I do not have that in the view model.

66
00:03:28,350 --> 00:03:30,630
We can add that to our view model,

67
00:03:30,630 --> 00:03:33,933
but that will depend on each shopping cart item.

68
00:03:35,160 --> 00:03:36,750
In a perfect situation,

69
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:40,200
we have to add that inside the shopping cart model.

70
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:41,820
Let me open that.

71
00:03:41,820 --> 00:03:44,760
And we do not want to add that to the database.

72
00:03:44,760 --> 00:03:47,550
We only want for display purposes,

73
00:03:47,550 --> 00:03:50,010
so we will add a double price,

74
00:03:50,010 --> 00:03:52,680
and we will add not mapped.

75
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:53,550
Because of that,

76
00:03:53,550 --> 00:03:56,580
it will not create this column in the database,

77
00:03:56,580 --> 00:03:58,530
and we are good.

78
00:03:58,530 --> 00:03:59,363
Now here,

79
00:03:59,363 --> 00:04:02,460
rather than storing that in double.price

80
00:04:02,460 --> 00:04:05,853
I will store that in cart.Price.

81
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:08,820
We will use that here,

82
00:04:08,820 --> 00:04:10,650
cart.Price.

83
00:04:10,650 --> 00:04:13,710
And that way we will have that particular price

84
00:04:13,710 --> 00:04:17,343
calculated and assigned inside the shopping cart.

85
00:04:18,510 --> 00:04:20,579
We have spent quite some time

86
00:04:20,579 --> 00:04:24,480
to get all the items for our shopping cart.

87
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:25,920
In the next video,

88
00:04:25,920 --> 00:04:30,300
let me replace everything that we have with a static HTML,

89
00:04:30,300 --> 00:04:34,530
with what we are passing here from the Index Action method.

90
00:04:34,530 --> 00:04:37,113
Which is a shopping cart view model.

